Field Detail

LINE_DELIMITER_NONE

public static final LineDelimiter LINE_DELIMITER_NONE
Enumerates the Line delimiter style for content. This will affect how the content is stored and retrieved.
  • NONE - no conversion on line delimiters, usually for binary data
  • LF - line terminators should become line feeds
  • CR - line terminators should become carriage returns
  • CRLF - line terminators should become carriage return, line feed pairs
  • PLATFORM - line terminators should become the terminator of the platform}

asQuery

public java.lang.String asQuery()
                         throws TeamRepositoryException
Returns a representation of this line delimiter suitable for use as a URI query parameter not requiring encoding (as opposed to the values returned by LineDelimiter.toString()). Note that LineDelimiter.LINE_DELIMITER_PLATFORM is not meaningful as a query parameter between client and server, and so is not supported here.

Returns:
Returns a query parameter representing this line delimiter. Never null. The empty string is returned for LineDelimiter.LINE_DELIMITER_NONE
Throws:
TeamRepositoryException
See Also:
LineDelimiter.fromQuery(String)

fromQuery

public static LineDelimiter fromQuery(java.lang.String query)
Returns the LineDelimiter corresponding the the referenced query string, as returned by LineDelimiter.asQuery().

Parameters:
query - A query string as returned by LineDelimiter.asQuery(). May be null or empty. If null or empty, LineDelimiter.LINE_DELIMITER_NONE is returned.
Returns:
The line delimiter for the referenced query string. Never null.
